<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="K_7796" type="Brief"><teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>Trevenen James Holland an Alfred Escher, London, Donnerstag, 27. Juni 1872</title></titleStmt><publicationStmt><p>Digitale Briefedition Alfred Escher, Zürich: Alfred Escher-Stiftung.</p></publicationStmt><sourceDesc><msDesc><msIdentifier><institution>SBB Historic</institution><idno>VGB_GB_SBBGB03_001</idno></msIdentifier></msDesc><bibl type="printed"/></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><textClass><keywords scheme="http://briefedition.alfred-escher.ch/keywords"><term>Tunnelbau</term><term>Gotthardtunnel</term><term>Eisenbahngesellschaften Offerten</term><term>Gotthardbahnprojekt</term></keywords></textClass><correspDesc><correspAction type="sent"><persName key="Holland Trevenen James" type="addressee">Trevenen James Holland</persName><persName key="Escher (vom Glas) Alfred" type="sender">Alfred Escher</persName><placeName>London</placeName><date when="1872-06-27">27. Juni 1872</date></correspAction><correspAction type="received"><placeName>Zürich</placeName></correspAction><correspContext><ref type="previous" target="B7740"/><ref type="next" target="B7777"/><ref type="previous-in-corresp" target="B7795"/><ptr type="context" target="4610 7793 7752 4611 7795 7796"/></correspContext></correspDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text><front>
      
        <p rend="left" xml:id="K_7796_p1"> <note type="addendum" xml:id="K_7796_c0">Nachträgliche Notiz oben links von dritter Hand mit Bleistift: <orig>ad Offerten aller Art.</orig> </note> <lb xml:id="p1-l1"/>
          <hi rend="printed">THE PATENT <lb xml:id="p1-l2"/>TUNNELING
        <lb xml:id="p1-l3"/>&amp; MINING MACHINE
        <lb xml:id="p1-l4"/>COMPANY.
        <lb xml:id="p1-l5"/>LIMITED</hi>
        </p>
      
      <div type="opener">
        <p rend="right" xml:id="K_7796_p2"><lb xml:id="p1-l6"/>
          <hi rend="printed">18. Finsbury Circus.</hi>
        </p>
      </div>
      <div type="dateline">
        <p rend="right" xml:id="K_7796_p3"><lb xml:id="p1-l7"/>
          <hi rend="printed">
            <placeName key="London (UK)">London</placeName>
            <choice><abbr>E. C.</abbr><expan>Eastern Central (östlicher Stadtteil)</expan></choice></hi>, <date when="1872-06-27">27<hi rend="sup">t</hi> June <hi rend="printed">187</hi>2</date> </p>
      </div>
      <div type="opener">
        <p rend="left" xml:id="K_7796_p4"><lb xml:id="p1-l8"/>From <choice><abbr>Lt: Colonel</abbr><expan>Lieutenant Colonel (Oberstleutnant)</expan></choice> Holland
        <lb xml:id="p1-l9"/>President
        <lb xml:id="p1-l10"/>of the Patent Tunneling &amp; Mining Machine <choice><abbr>C<hi rend="sup">o</hi> </abbr><expan>Compagnia / Compagnie / Company (Gesellschaft)</expan></choice> <choice><abbr>Ltd</abbr><expan>[with] Limited [liability] (mit beschränkter Haftung)</expan></choice> </p>
        <p rend="left" xml:id="K_7796_p5"><lb xml:id="p1-l11"/>To
        <lb xml:id="p1-l12"/><choice><abbr>Mons:</abbr><expan>Monsieur (Herr)</expan></choice> Le President
        <lb xml:id="p1-l13"/>of the <choice><abbr>St.</abbr><expan>Sankt / Sanct / Saint (heilig)</expan></choice> Gothard Railway Company
        <lb xml:id="p1-l14"/>Bellevue
        <lb xml:id="p1-l15"/><placeName key="Zürich (Stadt)">Zurich</placeName> <lb xml:id="p1-l16"/>Suisse</p>
      </div>
      <div type="opener">
        <p rend="left" xml:id="K_7796_p6"><lb xml:id="p1-l17"/>Sir</p>
      </div>
    </front><body>
      <p rend="indent" xml:id="K_7796_p7"><lb xml:id="p1-l18"/>With reference to the Tender sent in by this Company
        <lb xml:id="p1-l19"/>on <date when="1872-06-15">15. <choice><abbr>ult<hi rend="sup">o</hi> </abbr><expan>ultimo (letzten [Monats])</expan></choice></date> for boring the <placeName key="St. Gotthard (Pass)">St. Gothard</placeName> Tunnel I write to
        <lb xml:id="p1-l20"/>state that in the event of your requiring Boring Machines
        <lb xml:id="p1-l21"/>to be tested in Switzerland or elsewhere prior to the
        <lb xml:id="p1-l22"/>final acceptance of any Tender, my Company will be
        <lb xml:id="p1-l23"/>happy to send their Machine to any place you may
        <lb xml:id="p1-l24"/>name to test its capabilities on receiving from you
        <lb xml:id="p1-l25"/>or your Engineer-in-Chief an intimation that such is
        <lb xml:id="p1-l26"/>required.</p>
    </body><back>
      <div type="closer">
        <p rend="center" xml:id="K_7796_p8"><lb xml:id="p1-l27"/>I am, Sir
        <lb xml:id="p1-l28"/>Your most <choice><abbr>obed<hi rend="sup">t</hi> </abbr><expan>obedient (ergeben)</expan></choice> servant</p>
      </div>
      <div type="signature">
        <p rend="center" xml:id="K_7796_p9"><lb xml:id="p1-l29"/>Trev. Holland.
        <lb xml:id="p1-l30"/>
        <choice><abbr>Lt: Colonel</abbr><expan>Lieutenant Colonel (Oberstleutnant)</expan></choice>
        <lb xml:id="p1-l31"/>President</p> </div>
    </back></text></TEI>